Evraz Group, Polyus Gold, Rosneft: Russian Equity Preview

-- B y   D e n i s   M a t e r n o v s k y
-- 
2011-04-05T21:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-05/evraz-group-polyus-gold-rosneft-russian-equity-preview.html
The following companies may be
active in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
share prices are from the previous close of trading in Moscow.  The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  fell 0.2 percent to 1,848.21,
retreating from the highest level since June 2008, at the close
in Moscow. The dollar-denominated RTS Index declined 0.2 percent
to 2,088.64.  Evraz Group SA (EVR)  :  Russia ’s second-biggest steelmaker
said in a regulatory filing it seeks to purchase for cash the
outstanding amount of its $1.3 billion of dollar bonds due in
2013. Company global depositary receipts fell 1.2 percent to
$39.95 in  London .  OAO Polyus Gold (PLZL RX): Gold futures surged to a record
of $1,453.70 an ounce on the Comex in New York after trading
closed in Moscow. Russia’s biggest gold producer added 1.5
percent to 1,712 rubles.  OAO Rosneft (ROSN RX): Oil for May delivery dropped 0.5
percent to $107.91 a barrel in  New York , retreating from the
highest level in more than 30 months on signs demand may drop in
the U.S. and  China . Shares of Russia’s biggest oil company rose
0.4 percent to 267.47 rubles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Denis Maternovsky in Moscow at 
